Delta superinfection in patients with chronic hepatitis, liver cirrhosis and hepatocellular carcinoma in a Sahelian area. Study of 112 cases versus 46 controls. From October 1982 to June 1985 158 hospitalized patients in the National Hospital of Niamey, Republic of Niger, were selected whenever one of the following signs was found: hepatomegaly, jaundice, ascites, oesophageal varices, abdominal venous pattern, or splenomegaly. Investigations included hepatic echography (158/158), needle liver biopsy (68/158), radioimmunoassays for serum hepatitis B surface antigen (HBsAg 158/158), anti-HBs (152/158), anti-HBc (129/158) and anti-delta antibody (anti-HD